      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BERNARDO'S QUEEN (1) could manage only seventh at Bendigo last time but turned heads when posting a speedy 28.18 over 500m at Bendigo the start prior. Should be in this for a long way. WHO SHE RULES (2) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when seventh at Bendigo over 500m behind BERNARDO'S QUEEN (28.74) in a Restricted WIN H. Placed at her previous run. Comes through a solid form race last start. Has ability and can measure up. MISS MAXIMUS (3) flew the lids off the inside with a slick early split but ran over at the finish when a narrow fourth (22.37) over 390m at this track. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. LOVE YOU (8) is building a nice sequence of placings and will be in the mix again.",
